picoctf Bypass Me writeup

1.understand lldb command 

2.use "ssh ctf-player@foggy-cliff.picoctf.net -p port" to connect 

3.and try to run bypassme.bin and its filter function 

4.we can know it filters out all chars except letters

5.so we might need to reverse and get the password

run it with lldb => lldb ./bypassme.bin
disassemble main function => disassemble --name main

6.we know its decode_password function will return a real password , so we need to set a breakpoint there

set breakpoint => b decode_password
run it => r
now we are in decode_password function
finish running this function => finish
now its return value is password 
print out its password => expr (char*)($rbp - 0x110)
stop lldb => quit

7.run bypassme.bin and input the password

8.get flag!
